    en: "Jose received a notice from Monroe County DHS that his SNAP benefits would be cut from $200 to $90 per month starting on the 1st. The notice arrived 8 days before the effective date. He went to otda.ny.gov/hearings the same day, filed the request online with his case number and a one-sentence reason ('the agency counted income I no longer receive'), and checked yes for aid continuing. He got a confirmation number immediately. Aid continuing kept his SNAP at $200 while he waited. The hearing was held by phone 6 weeks later. He brought a recent pay stub showing his hours had been cut. The hearing officer ruled in his favor and reversed the SNAP reduction. Retroactive benefits restored what he would have lost in the first month."
